# iOS input focus zoom

Safari on iPhone zooms the viewport when a focused `input`, `textarea`, or `select` has a **computed font-size below 16px**.

- Use at least **`text-base` (16px)** on editable fields, or explicit `text-[16px]`.
- Do not use `text-sm` / `text-xs` on the actual `<input>` / `<textarea>` / `<select>` element (labels can stay smaller).
- `globals.css` already sets a `max(16px, 1em)` floor in `@layer base` as a backup; prefer correct Tailwind classes so design stays intentional.
